Czech Ministry Gets $3.2 Billion Offer in Environmental Tender

-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 
2011-09-13T12:24:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-13/czech-ministry-gets-3-2-billion-offer-in-environmental-tender.html
The Czech Finance Ministry said
Marius Pedersen Engineering AS submitted the lowest contract
price of 56.8 billion koruna ($3.2 billion) at a tender for
environmental services.  Geosan Group AS offered its services for 57.8 billion
koruna and Environmental Services AS lodged contract price of
65.5 billion koruna, the ministry said today in a statement. The
winner of the tender, which is seeking a company to manage a
cleanup of polluted sites in the country, still requires
government approval.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague 
 lponikelska1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
